    <div class="img_wrap">
        <img data-original="https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2019/02/25/ap_19052796928811_wide-fa8b17de940b77303a8ae7df50b5c97c83466af7-s1200.jpg" alt="" />
    </div>
</div>
<div class="enlarge_html">
    <div class="image_data">
        <p class="caption">Michael Cohen, President Trump's former personal attorney, is due to meet with members of Congress over three days in Washington. The political stakes are high for both Democrats and Republicans.</p>
        <span class="credit" aria-label="Image credit">
            
            Susan Walsh/AP
            
        </span>
    </div>
</div>
   </div>
   <p>Members of Congress have some questions this week for Michael Cohen.</p>   <p>President Trump's former personal lawyer is set to begin a three-day marathon on Tuesday that will take him behind closed doors with the Senate intelligence committee, then before an open session of the House oversight committee on Wednesday and then to a closed House intelligence committee session on Thursday.</p>   <p>The public hearing on Wednesday could become a three-ring spectacle and will be the first big televised show for an oversight committee that has vowed to spend the next two years on intense investigations of Trump.</p>   <p>With Cohen, Democrats want to tease out evidence of wrongdoing by Trump while Republicans want to damage Cohen's credibility so much that no one can believe anything he says.</p>   <p>The situation is more complicated than simple politics as usual, however: Members are supposed to be bound by guidelines agreed to with the Justice Department about the topics Cohen can discuss.</p>   <aside id="ad-backstage-wrap" aria-label="advertisement">
    

    <div id="ad-backstage-News_National_National_Security" class="ad-backstage" data-ad-config='{"network":"\/6735\/","site":{"default":"n6735.NPR","mobile":"n6735.NPRMOBILE"},"zone":"News_National_National_Security","targets":{"testserver":"false","isPodcastEpisode":"false","storyId":"697707393","agg":["312150170","191676894","434975886"]},"location":"backstage","deferred":false,"isBetweenContent":true,"isAggSponsorship":false,"borderClass":""}'></div>

</aside>   <div id="res697815366" class="bucketwrap internallink insettwocolumn inset2col ">
            <div class="bucket img">
                  <a id="featuredStackSquareImage696428301" href="https://www.npr.org/2019/02/22/696428301/heres-what-may-happen-when-the-mueller-investigation-is-completed"  data-metrics='{"category":"Story to Story","action":"Click Internal Link","label":"https:\/\/www.npr.org\/2019\/02\/22\/696428301\/heres-what-may-happen-when-the-mueller-investigation-is-completed"}' ><img src="https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2019/02/21/gettyimages-699393960_sq-81e78b1ca09bef3a5968c8ee1f168f71cf535f7b-s100-c15.jpg" data-original="https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2019/02/21/gettyimages-699393960_sq-81e78b1ca09bef3a5968c8ee1f168f71cf535f7b-s100.jpg" class="img lazyOnLoad"  alt="Here's What May Happen When The Mueller Investigation Is Completed" /></a>         <div class="bucketblock">
                        <h3 class="slug"><a href="https://www.npr.org/sections/national-security/">National Security </a></h3>
            <h3><a href="https://www.npr.org/2019/02/22/696428301/heres-what-may-happen-when-the-mueller-investigation-is-completed"  data-metrics='{"category":"Story to Story","action":"Click Internal Link","label":"https:\/\/www.npr.org\/2019\/02\/22\/696428301\/heres-what-may-happen-when-the-mueller-investigation-is-completed"}' >Here's What May Happen When The Mueller Investigation Is Completed</a></h3>
         </div>
         
<!-- END CLASS="BUCKETBLOCK" -->
      </div>
      
<!-- END CLASS="BUCKET IMG" -->
   </div>
   
<!-- END ID="RES697815366" CLASS="BUCKETWRAP INTERNALLINK INSETTWOCOLUMN INSET2COL " -->
   <p>Oversight committee Chairman Elijah Cummings, D-Md., said that Russia's interference in the 2016 election will be off limits but members may ask Cohen about "the president's payoffs, financial disclosures, compliance with campaign finance laws, business practices, and other matters."</p>   <div id="res697816130" class="bucketwrap internallink mediapromo primary">
            <h4 class="internallink__slug">Politics</h4>
