   </div>
   
<!-- END ID="RES697817398" CLASS="BUCKETWRAP INTERNALLINK INSETTWOCOLUMN INSET2COL " -->
   <p><a href="https://www.npr.org/2018/05/02/607943366/giuliani-says-trump-did-know-about-stormy-daniels-payment">Trump has acknowledged a payment to one woman</a> but denies the underlying allegations by both women about sexual relationships.</p>   <p>The president also argues that the actions Cohen admitted in his plea deal, which implicated Trump, weren't against the law — that he, in effect, pleaded guilty to crimes that aren't crimes. The judge in his case, however, supervised the plea and <a href="https://www.npr.org/2018/12/12/676040070/michael-cohen-sentenced-to-3-years-in-prison-following-plea-that-implicated-trum">sentenced Cohen to three years in prison</a>.</p>   <p>Cohen was scheduled to report to prison early next month but sought an extension, citing his recovery from shoulder surgery and the need to prepare for this week's extended visit to Capitol Hill.</p>   <div id="res697818953" class="bucketwrap internallink insettwocolumn inset2col ">
            <div class="bucket img">
                  <a id="featuredStackSquareImage671864979" href="https://www.npr.org/2018/11/29/671864979/trump-moscow-real-estate-talks-continued-into-presidential-run-documents-show"  data-metrics='{"category":"Story to Story","action":"Click Internal Link","label":"https:\/\/www.npr.org\/2018\/11\/29\/671864979\/trump-moscow-real-estate-talks-continued-into-presidential-run-documents-show"}' ><img src="https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2018/11/29/ap_18333556991496_sq-ce201ba3d2c0273d9229536c9f98f44ae0cf2ab9-s100-c15.jpg" data-original="https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2018/11/29/ap_18333556991496_sq-ce201ba3d2c0273d9229536c9f98f44ae0cf2ab9-s100.jpg" class="img lazyOnLoad"  alt="Michael Cohen Admits Trump Tower-Moscow Talks Continued Well Into 2016 Campaign" /></a>         <div class="bucketblock">
                        <h3 class="slug"><a href="https://www.npr.org/sections/national-security/">National Security </a></h3>
            <h3><a href="https://www.npr.org/2018/11/29/671864979/trump-moscow-real-estate-talks-continued-into-presidential-run-documents-show"  data-metrics='{"category":"Story to Story","action":"Click Internal Link","label":"https:\/\/www.npr.org\/2018\/11\/29\/671864979\/trump-moscow-real-estate-talks-continued-into-presidential-run-documents-show"}' >Michael Cohen Admits Trump Tower-Moscow Talks Continued Well Into 2016 Campaign</a></h3>
         </div>
         
<!-- END CLASS="BUCKETBLOCK" -->
      </div>
      
<!-- END CLASS="BUCKET IMG" -->
   </div>
   
<!-- END ID="RES697818953" CLASS="BUCKETWRAP INTERNALLINK INSETTWOCOLUMN INSET2COL " -->
   <p><a href="https://www.npr.org/2018/11/29/671864979/trump-moscow-real-estate-talks-continued-into-presidential-run-documents-show">Cohen also has pleaded guilty to lying to Congress</a> about the negotiations he conducted on behalf of Trump's business with powerful Russians as part of a potential Trump Tower real estate project in Moscow.</p>   <p>Cohen first told lawmakers those talks wound up in early 2016, when actually they continued well into the campaign — almost to the point at which Trump became the Republican nominee for president.</p>   <div id="res697819762" class="bucketwrap internallink insettwocolumn inset2col ">
            <div class="bucket img">
                  <a id="featuredStackSquareImage586099619" href="https://www.npr.org/2018/04/25/586099619/the-russia-investigations-what-you-need-to-know-about-russian-active-measures"  data-metrics='{"category":"Story to Story","action":"Click Internal Link","label":"https:\/\/www.npr.org\/2018\/04\/25\/586099619\/the-russia-investigations-what-you-need-to-know-about-russian-active-measures"}' ><img src="https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2018/04/18/gettyimages-717158013_sq-588464b224c6a16b3999c7c1433f879e663cb5b6-s100-c15.jpg" data-original="https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2018/04/18/gettyimages-717158013_sq-588464b224c6a16b3999c7c1433f879e663cb5b6-s100.jpg" class="img lazyOnLoad"  alt="The Russia Investigations: What You Need To Know About Russian 'Active Measures'" /></a>         <div class="bucketblock">
                        <h3 class="slug"><a href="https://www.npr.org/sections/national-security/">National Security </a></h3>
            <h3><a href="https://www.npr.org/2018/04/25/586099619/the-russia-investigations-what-you-need-to-know-about-russian-active-measures"  data-metrics='{"category":"Story to Story","action":"Click Internal Link","label":"https:\/\/www.npr.org\/2018\/04\/25\/586099619\/the-russia-investigations-what-you-need-to-know-about-russian-active-measures"}' >The Russia Investigations: What You Need To Know About Russian 'Active Measures'</a></h3>
         </div>
         
<!-- END CLASS="BUCKETBLOCK" -->
      </div>
      
<!-- END CLASS="BUCKET IMG" -->
   </div>
   
<!-- END ID="RES697819762" CLASS="BUCKETWRAP INTERNALLINK INSETTWOCOLUMN INSET2COL " -->
   <p>That meant Trump's business was continuing to negotiate with Russians even as the Russian government had launched its campaign of "<a href="https://www.npr.org/2018/04/25/586099619/the-russia-investigations-what-you-need-to-know-about-russian-active-measures">active measures</a>" against the presidential election — and even as <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2018/11/29/us/politics/fact-check-cohen-trump-.html">Trump was denying, in 2016, that he had any dealings with Russia</a>.</p>   <p>The president has since said that he decided on his own <a href="https://www.whitehouse.gov/briefings-statements/remarks-president-trump-marine-one-departure-27/">not to go forward with Trump Tower Moscow</a> and that his denials were appropriate because there was no final deal.<strong> </strong>The building was never built.</p>   <p><strong>A likely minefield</strong></p>   <p>The challenge for Cummings and the other members of the oversight committee may be in navigating which subject matters fall on which side of the line they have drawn with Justice Department special counsel Robert Mueller.</p>   <div id="res697822763" class="bucketwrap internallink insettwocolumn inset2col ">
            <div class="bucket img">
                  <a id="featuredStackSquareImage643444815" href="https://www.npr.org/2018/12/09/643444815/all-the-criminal-charges-to-emerge-so-far-from-robert-muellers-investigation"  data-metrics='{"category":"Story to Story","action":"Click Internal Link","label":"https:\/\/www.npr.org\/2018\/12\/09\/643444815\/all-the-criminal-charges-to-emerge-so-far-from-robert-muellers-investigation"}' ><img src="https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2018/09/14/gettyimages-699394184_sq-1167adf710eb3307517d2ab174f9c424d263b0e1-s100-c15.jpg" data-original="https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2018/09/14/gettyimages-699394184_sq-1167adf710eb3307517d2ab174f9c424d263b0e1-s100.jpg" class="img lazyOnLoad"  alt="All The Criminal Charges To Emerge From Robert Mueller's Investigation" /></a>         <div class="bucketblock">
                        <h3 class="slug"><a href="https://www.npr.org/sections/national-security/">National Security </a></h3>
            <h3><a href="https://www.npr.org/2018/12/09/643444815/all-the-criminal-charges-to-emerge-so-far-from-robert-muellers-investigation"  data-metrics='{"category":"Story to Story","action":"Click Internal Link","label":"https:\/\/www.npr.org\/2018\/12\/09\/643444815\/all-the-criminal-charges-to-emerge-so-far-from-robert-muellers-investigation"}' >All The Criminal Charges To Emerge So Far From Robert Mueller's Investigation</a></h3>
         </div>
         
<!-- END CLASS="BUCKETBLOCK" -->
      </div>
      
<!-- END CLASS="BUCKET IMG" -->
   </div>
   
<!-- END ID="RES697822763" CLASS="BUCKETWRAP INTERNALLINK INSETTWOCOLUMN INSET2COL " -->
   <p>Cohen, meanwhile, may offer implicit clues about which areas are connected with alleged collusion in the questions that he agrees to answer and those to which he demurs. </p>   <p>The degree to which he addresses Trump Tower Moscow, for example, could offer suggestions about how closely it may be connected with the focus of Mueller's investigators.</p>   <p>And Republicans on the oversight committee — many of whom are hostile toward Mueller, the Justice Department and Cohen — may not necessarily feel bound by any ground rules.</p>   <p>Ranking member Rep. Jim Jordan, R-Ohio, has vowed that Republicans will ask what they want to ask. </p>   <p>"I have serious process concerns with this hearing," Jordan said. "I will not stand by quietly while an admitted liar comes before the committee. Our members intend to question Mr. Cohen about the crimes he pleaded guilty to, other criminal activity he participated in but refused to disclose, his international financial dealings, and a long list of other probative activities."</p>   <p>The intricate procedural ground on which this battle is to be fought may make the Wednesday session another master class in congressional procedure. Republicans may attempt to use points of order, objections or other roadblocks to try to adjourn or constrain the proceedings.</p>   <div id="res697830107" class="bucketwrap internallink insettwocolumn inset2col ">
            <div class="bucket img">
                  <a id="featuredStackSquareImage697391538" href="https://www.npr.org/2019/02/23/697391538/paul-manafort-brazenly-broke-the-law-special-counsel-says-in-sentencing-memo"  data-metrics='{"category":"Story to Story","action":"Click Internal Link","label":"https:\/\/www.npr.org\/2019\/02\/23\/697391538\/paul-manafort-brazenly-broke-the-law-special-counsel-says-in-sentencing-memo"}' ><img src="https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2019/02/23/ap_92198304282_sq-9171b60ef0d87727e4da5c891be82513969925f3-s100-c15.jpg" data-original="https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2019/02/23/ap_92198304282_sq-9171b60ef0d87727e4da5c891be82513969925f3-s100.jpg" class="img lazyOnLoad"  alt="Paul Manafort 'Brazenly' Broke The Law, Special Counsel Says In Sentencing Memo" /></a>         <div class="bucketblock">
                        <h3 class="slug"><a href="https://www.npr.org/sections/national/">National </a></h3>
            <h3><a href="https://www.npr.org/2019/02/23/697391538/paul-manafort-brazenly-broke-the-law-special-counsel-says-in-sentencing-memo"  data-metrics='{"category":"Story to Story","action":"Click Internal Link","label":"https:\/\/www.npr.org\/2019\/02\/23\/697391538\/paul-manafort-brazenly-broke-the-law-special-counsel-says-in-sentencing-memo"}' >Paul Manafort 'Brazenly' Broke The Law, Special Counsel Says In Sentencing Memo</a></h3>
         </div>
         
<!-- END CLASS="BUCKETBLOCK" -->
      </div>
      
<!-- END CLASS="BUCKET IMG" -->
   </div>
   
<!-- END ID="RES697830107" CLASS="BUCKETWRAP INTERNALLINK INSETTWOCOLUMN INSET2COL " -->
   <p>Democrats can use their majority to keep the show going, but if they must take recorded votes or other procedural steps each time there is an objection, that could mean the Cohen hearing lasts for hours.</p>   <p>Democrats tried to use their own objections, points of order and other procedural obstacles when Republicans controlled the majority in the House, including at a hearing of the House Judiciary Committee with former FBI Special Agent Peter Strzok.</p>   <p>Now the shoe is on the other foot.</p>   <p><strong>A witness — but for whom?</strong></p>   <p>Cohen is a politically problematic witness for both Democrats and Republicans.</p>   <p>His admissions about lying mean there is often scope for one side or the other to discount something he has said. Even prosecutors involved in his plea agreement in New York City complained they believed Cohen had more knowledge about wrongdoing than he admitted.</p>   <div id="res697831033" class="bucketwrap internallink insettwocolumn inset2col ">
            <div class="bucket img">
                  <a id="featuredStackSquareImage695112668" href="https://www.npr.org/2019/02/18/695112668/andrew-mccabe-ex-fbi-deputy-describes-remarkable-number-of-trump-russia-contacts"  data-metrics='{"category":"Story to Story","action":"Click Internal Link","label":"https:\/\/www.npr.org\/2019\/02\/18\/695112668\/andrew-mccabe-ex-fbi-deputy-describes-remarkable-number-of-trump-russia-contacts"}' ><img src="https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2019/02/15/_dsc0018_sq-52cf7219b1a81b0889e313c2b5d3bcccbf3830c7-s100-c15.jpg" data-original="https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2019/02/15/_dsc0018_sq-52cf7219b1a81b0889e313c2b5d3bcccbf3830c7-s100.jpg" class="img lazyOnLoad"  alt="Andrew McCabe, Ex-FBI Deputy, Describes 'Remarkable' Number Of Trump-Russia Contacts" /></a>         <div class="bucketblock">
                        <h3 class="slug"><a href="https://www.npr.org/sections/national-security/">National Security </a></h3>
            <h3><a href="https://www.npr.org/2019/02/18/695112668/andrew-mccabe-ex-fbi-deputy-describes-remarkable-number-of-trump-russia-contacts"  data-metrics='{"category":"Story to Story","action":"Click Internal Link","label":"https:\/\/www.npr.org\/2019\/02\/18\/695112668\/andrew-mccabe-ex-fbi-deputy-describes-remarkable-number-of-trump-russia-contacts"}' >Andrew McCabe, Ex-FBI Deputy, Describes 'Remarkable' Number Of Trump-Russia Contacts</a></h3>
         </div>
         
<!-- END CLASS="BUCKETBLOCK" -->
      </div>
      
<!-- END CLASS="BUCKET IMG" -->
   </div>
   
<!-- END ID="RES697831033" CLASS="BUCKETWRAP INTERNALLINK INSETTWOCOLUMN INSET2COL " -->
   <p>Exhibit A could be the role described for him in the infamous, partly unverified <a href="https://www.npr.org/2018/04/25/586040491/what-you-need-to-know-about-the-russia-investigations-the-dossier">Russia dossier</a> that appeared in early 2017, earlier in the Russia imbroglio.</p>   <p>NPR has never detailed the document because so much of it remains unproved, but, in general terms, it describes travel by Cohen as part of an alleged conspiracy between Trump's inner circle and the Russian attack on the 2016 election.</p>   <p>Cohen told Congress on an earlier visit, when he was still loyal to Trump, that he denied that account. He also has said publicly <a href="https://twitter.com/MichaelCohen212/status/1078400493494390784">several times since</a> then that he didn't take part in the travel described in the dossier.</p>   <div id="res697714765" class="bucketwrap twitter large graphic624" aria-label="Tweet">
            <blockquote class="twitter-tweet"><p lang="en" dir="ltr">I hear <a href="https://twitter.com/hashtag/Prague?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">#Prague</a> <a href="https://twitter.com/hashtag/CzechRepublic?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">#CzechRepublic</a> is beautiful in the summertime. I wouldn’t know as I have never been. <a href="https://twitter.com/hashtag/Mueller?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">#Mueller</a> knows everything!</p>&mdash; Michael Cohen (@MichaelCohen212) <a href="https://twitter.com/MichaelCohen212/status/1078400493494390784?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">December 27, 2018</a></blockquote>
<script async src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script>
   </div>
   
<!-- END ID="RES697714765" CLASS="BUCKETWRAP TWITTER LARGE GRAPHIC624" ARIA-LABEL="TWEET" -->
   <p>Cohen's denial helps Republicans who are eager to dismiss the dossier as baseless rumormongering and to undercut the basic premise of the Russia investigation being conducted by Mueller — that people like Cohen, working for Trump, may have colluded with the Russians.</p>   <p>But the degree to which Jordan or other Republican members attempt to reinforce those denials by Cohen complicates attempts to paint him as a liar in other ways — although that may not stop individual members from pursuing their own lines of questioning.</p>   <div id="res697831977" class="bucketwrap internallink insettwocolumn inset2col ">
            <div class="bucket img">
                  <a id="featuredStackSquareImage696770940" href="https://www.npr.org/2019/02/21/696770940/roger-stone-barred-from-talking-about-his-case-following-criticism-of-judge"  data-metrics='{"category":"Story to Story","action":"Click Internal Link","label":"https:\/\/www.npr.org\/2019\/02\/21\/696770940\/roger-stone-barred-from-talking-about-his-case-following-criticism-of-judge"}' ><img src="https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2019/02/21/ap_19052775229153_sq-4d1c5e4837a34729ec13571a1042a3b335b78d58-s100-c15.jpg" data-original="https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2019/02/21/ap_19052775229153_sq-4d1c5e4837a34729ec13571a1042a3b335b78d58-s100.jpg" class="img lazyOnLoad"  alt="Roger Stone Barred From Talking About His Case Following Criticism Of Judge" /></a>         <div class="bucketblock">
                        <h3 class="slug"><a href="https://www.npr.org/sections/law/">Law </a></h3>
            <h3><a href="https://www.npr.org/2019/02/21/696770940/roger-stone-barred-from-talking-about-his-case-following-criticism-of-judge"  data-metrics='{"category":"Story to Story","action":"Click Internal Link","label":"https:\/\/www.npr.org\/2019\/02\/21\/696770940\/roger-stone-barred-from-talking-about-his-case-following-criticism-of-judge"}' >Roger Stone Barred From Talking About His Case Following Criticism Of Judge</a></h3>
         </div>
         
<!-- END CLASS="BUCKETBLOCK" -->
      </div>
      
<!-- END CLASS="BUCKET IMG" -->
   </div>
   
<!-- END ID="RES697831977" CLASS="BUCKETWRAP INTERNALLINK INSETTWOCOLUMN INSET2COL " -->
   <p>The inverse is true for Democrats and opponents of Trump: Cohen's denials about his travel were met with deep skepticism among people who believe the evidence is already clear about alleged collusion.</p>   <p>NPR asked Cummings on Monday whether he expected Cohen would be a credible witness.</p>   <p>"We don't know," he said.</p>   <p>But the public clearly has an interest in getting his testimony on the record in the open, Cummings said.</p>   <p>"I practiced law for more than 20 years and you have a situation where a man, apparently, wants to bare his soul and talk about his relationship with this president," he told NPR's <em>All Things Considered</em>.</p>   <p>"But keep in mind, Michael Cohen is the one person who has accused the president of committing a crime. It's hard to say what's going to happen. But the good thing about it is that members of Congress will have an opportunity to observe him. The public will have an opportunity to observe him. And I think that's a good thing."</p>   <div id="res697832661" class="bucketwrap internallink insettwocolumn inset2col ">
            <div class="bucket img">
                  <a id="featuredStackSquareImage694751343" href="https://www.npr.org/2019/02/14/694751343/senate-confirms-william-barr-as-next-attorney-general"  data-metrics='{"category":"Story to Story","action":"Click Internal Link","label":"https:\/\/www.npr.org\/2019\/02\/14\/694751343\/senate-confirms-william-barr-as-next-attorney-general"}' ><img src="https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2019/02/14/gettyimages-1091785730_sq-8847b8c34d9b25aedc1563aa453dc9ef690e31b9-s100-c15.jpg" data-original="https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2019/02/14/gettyimages-1091785730_sq-8847b8c34d9b25aedc1563aa453dc9ef690e31b9-s100.jpg" class="img lazyOnLoad"  alt="Attorney General William Barr Swears Oath Of Office After Senate Confirmation" /></a>         <div class="bucketblock">
                        <h3 class="slug"><a href="https://www.npr.org/sections/law/">Law </a></h3>
            <h3><a href="https://www.npr.org/2019/02/14/694751343/senate-confirms-william-barr-as-next-attorney-general"  data-metrics='{"category":"Story to Story","action":"Click Internal Link","label":"https:\/\/www.npr.org\/2019\/02\/14\/694751343\/senate-confirms-william-barr-as-next-attorney-general"}' >Attorney General William Barr Swears Oath Of Office After Senate Confirmation</a></h3>
         </div>
         
<!-- END CLASS="BUCKETBLOCK" -->
      </div>
      
<!-- END CLASS="BUCKET IMG" -->
   </div>
   
<!-- END ID="RES697832661" CLASS="BUCKETWRAP INTERNALLINK INSETTWOCOLUMN INSET2COL " -->
